---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title={"Terms of Service — Kingdom Bible Study"} description={"Terms for using Kingdom Bible Study: a free personal Bible study application. Your data stays yours, stored in your browser and your own Google Drive."}>
<Fragment slot="head-end">
<style is:inline>
  .policy-page { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 4rem; }
  .policy-page h1 { font-size: 1.7rem; margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .policy-page .policy-date { font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .policy-page h2 { font-size: 1.15rem; margin: 2rem 0 0.6rem; }
  .policy-page p, .policy-page li { font-size: 0.98rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .policy-page ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .policy-page li { margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
  .policy-page a { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
</Fragment>
<main>
  <div class="container policy-page">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="policy-date">Effective July 11, 2026 · kingdombiblestudy.com</p>

    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      Kingdom Bible Study is a free, personal Bible study application: a
      scripture reader, study tools, devotionals, a classic-text library, and
      private tracking of your own study life. By using the site you accept
      these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Your data is yours</h2>
    <p>
      Everything you create here — progress, prayers, notes, highlights,
      journal entries, and the rest — belongs to you. It is stored in your
      browser and, if you enable sync, in <strong>your own Google Drive</strong>,
      solely so you can continue your study across devices. The site never
      evaluates, shares, or sells your data, and its operator has no access to
      it. See the <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for the full details.
    </p>

    <h2>Your responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Your Google account and its security are yours to manage; sync
        requires a working Google sign-in on each device you use.</li>
      <li>Backups are under your control — if you delete the backup file, revoke
        the app's access, or clear your browser storage on every device, your
        data cannot be recovered by anyone.</li>
      <li>Use the site for personal, non-commercial study.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Content</h2>
    <p>
      Scripture texts, dictionaries, and library documents are public-domain
      works or are used under their stated licenses; provenance — including
      where AI assistance was used in preparing study material — is documented
      on the <a href="/about/">About &amp; AI Transparency</a> page. Study
      content is offered for personal edification and is not professional
      advice of any kind.
    </p>

    <h2>The service</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The site is provided free, <strong>"as is" and "as available"</strong>,
        without warranties of any kind, express or implied.</li>
      <li>Features may change, break, or be discontinued at any time; the site
        may be updated without notice.</li>
      <li>To the maximum extent permitted by law, the site's operator is not
        liable for any damages arising from use of the site, including loss of
        data — please keep sync enabled or export what matters to you.</li>
      <li>Third-party services you choose to connect (Google sign-in, Google
        Drive) are governed by their own terms and policies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If these terms change, the new version will be posted at this address
      with an updated effective date. Questions can be raised on the
      <a href="https://github.com/seriousd6/Seriousd6.github.io">project's
      GitHub repository</a>.
    </p>

    <p><a href="/privacy/">← Privacy Policy</a></p>
  </div>
</main>
</Base>
